  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "瑣事定律 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-law-of-triviality",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / meetings / attention / governance</p>\n    <h1>瑣事定律</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Law of Triviality</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">團隊常把最多討論時間花在最容易理解、最容易表態的小事上，反而讓真正高風險的大題目被快速帶過。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要幫你看見：會議時間不一定跟議題重要性成比例，往往更跟大家能不能輕鬆發言成比例。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>組織現象 / 注意力錯配</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Groups spend more time on easier, smaller issues</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>理解門檻、表態成本、議題風險、時間分配</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在會議與 review 裡主動校正『大家討論最久的，未必最重要』</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>容易</span>\n      <span>討論</span>\n      <span>失焦</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>越容易說話的題目，越容易吃掉整場會議</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">瑣事定律抓到的是組織注意力的偏斜，不是因為大家愚蠢，而是因為參與門檻不同。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>高風險議題往往需要專業、準備與承擔，而油漆顏色、命名與小流程則人人都能出聲；結果時間分配反而顛倒。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先看誰容易開口</strong>\n        <p>能被所有人快速理解的議題，最容易長成長討論。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再看誰真正承擔風險</strong>\n        <p>真正大的決策常只剩少數人有足夠背景與責任感能深入說。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後用流程校正</strong>\n        <p>若不主動設計時間與決策權重，注意力自然會往瑣事聚集。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一場被小事拖走的會議開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這個定律經典得近乎日常：真正昂貴的問題常被十分鐘帶過，瑣碎細節卻聊半小時。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>架構風險、法規依賴與資料遷移只花了十幾分鐘，反而 button 文案與 naming 聊到會議超時。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>不是小事不重要，而是它們因為人人都懂、人人都能評價，天然比較會搶時間。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">議題理解門檻低</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">更多人樂於發言</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">時間被從重要但難懂的題目抽走</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>瑣事定律最實際的用法，是把會議時間當作稀缺資源來保護，而不是任它被可發言性牽引。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看注意力錯配的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">想判斷一場討論是不是落進這個模式，可以先看這四個訊號。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>低門檻議題過度膨脹</strong>\n        <p>越容易形成個人品味意見，越容易聊不停。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>高門檻議題被快速帶過</strong>\n        <p>真正複雜的問題因為少數人懂，反而沒被集體追問。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>參與感替代了風險感</strong>\n        <p>大家對能參與的題目更有存在感，未必代表那是更大的風險。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>缺乏主持校正</strong>\n        <p>若主持不主動控時與切題，討論自然滑向大家都能講的地方。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>議題類型</th>\n            <th>討論時看起來像</th>\n            <th>真正風險</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>命名與樣式</td>\n            <td>意見很多、很熱烈</td>\n            <td>容易吃掉核心設計風險的時間</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>架構與法規依賴</td>\n            <td>很快點頭帶過</td>\n            <td>若判斷錯，代價遠高於瑣碎細節</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>流程小優化</td>\n            <td>每個人都有感</td>\n            <td>容易把會議變成零碎偏好交換</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>高成本決策</td>\n            <td>只有少數人發言</td>\n            <td>沉默不代表理解，只代表門檻高</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼大家都比較想聊油漆，不想聊發電機</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為能懂、能講、能表現存在感的題目，本來就更容易聚集注意力。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>可參與感很誘人</strong>\n        <p>對人人看得懂的題目發表意見，能快速產生自己有貢獻的感覺。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>複雜題目有挫敗感</strong>\n        <p>若議題需要很多背景，人就更容易沉默或假裝已經理解。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>主持若不切題，熱度就會勝出</strong>\n        <p>熱鬧不代表重要，只代表表態成本低。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">這條定律不是貶低小事，而是提醒你：時間分配若不被設計，就不會自然接近風險分配。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把注意力管理帶回會議設計</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">工程組織裡最常見的版本，是 architecture review 被 bikeshedding，真正的邊界條件反而沒被說清楚。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Design review</strong>\n        <p>UI 細節與命名往往比 failure mode 更容易引發集體討論。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Roadmap 規劃</strong>\n        <p>功能排序聊很久，實際依賴、法規與 migration cost 卻沒有同等時間。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>PR 討論</strong>\n        <p>格式與小重構最容易收到大量 comment，關鍵假設與風險可能反而被滑過。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>對高風險議題預留保護時段與明確 owner，避免它被會議熱點吃掉。</li>\n      <li>把可非同步處理的瑣碎題目移出主會議，讓同步時間留給難而重要的判斷。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>別把它當成『小事都不重要』</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">真正的問題不是小事存在，而是小事和大事搶了錯的比例。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>所以細節不用管</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。細節也重要，只是未必要占用最稀缺的同步決策時間。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要熱烈討論就是壞事</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>熱烈沒問題，前提是它沒有吃掉對高風險問題的必要注意力。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>解法是禁止大家發言</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>更好的做法是調整議程結構，而不是壓低參與。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>這場會議在解真正昂貴的問題嗎</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>我們現在聊最久的，是最重要的，還是只是最好聊的</strong>\n        <p>若把議題成本與影響排一遍，時間分配還合理嗎？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>真正高風險的問題，有沒有被同等程度追問</strong>\n        <p>是不是因為太難、太少人懂，就被草率點頭帶過了？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可看 bikeshedding、meeting design 與 decision hygiene；也可以把這頁接到 review 流程治理。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 Parkinson 提出的 law of triviality 為主，再用 bikeshedding 這個工程圈常見版本補上現場語感。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Law of triviality 條目整理了為什麼群體容易在小事上耗掉 disproportionate 的注意力。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_of_triviality\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Law of Triviality</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>工程語彙</strong>\n        <p>FreeBSD FAQ 的 bikeshed 段落，是工程圈最常引用的現代版本。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://docs.freebsd.org/en/books/faq/misc/#bikeshed-painting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Why Bicyclesheds Are Blue</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>鄰近脈絡</strong>\n        <p>Parkinson&#x27;s law 可作為對照，看到時間與注意力如何被組織機制一起塑形。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parkinson%27s_law\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Parkinson&#x27;s Law</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後很適合回頭看最近一場長會議，重算一次各議題用時，看看時間分配有沒有真的對應風險分配。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
